 by renowned Rumi scholar A. J. Arberry, who provides here one of the most comprehensive and adept English translations of this enigmatic genius. Mystical Poems is the definitive resource for anyone seeking an introduction to or an enriched understanding of one of the world’s greatest poets. “Rumi is one of the world’s greatest lyrical poets in any language—as well as probably the most accessible and approachable representative of Islamic civilization for Western students.”—James W. Morris, Oberlin College  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aSufi poetry, PersianvTranslations into English. 7aRELIGION / General.2bisacsh1 aArberry, A. J.1 aArberry, A. J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJavadi, Hasan.1 aLewis, Franklin D.1 aLewis, Franklin D., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aYarshater, Ehsan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aYarshater, Ehsan, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311063538640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226731636423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780226731636.jpg  a978-3-11-063538-6  University of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles